Interface EstimatableModel<I,D>

  • Type Parameters:
    I - type of independent data
    D - type of dependent data
    All Superinterfaces:

    AffineTransformModel, AffineTransformModel3d, FundamentalModel, GaussianVectorNaiveBayesModel, HistogramPatchModel, HistogramPixelModel, HomographyModel, LeastSquaresLinearModel, LinearRegression, MBFPatchClassificationModel, MBFPixelClassificationModel, NullModel, OrthotopePixelModel, PatchClassificationModel, PixelClassificationModel, RigidTransformModel3d, SimplePerceptron, SingleGaussianPixelModel, UnivariateGaussianNaiveBayesModel

    public interface EstimatableModel<I,D>
extends Model<I,D>, Cloneable
    An extension to a Model that allows the model to be estimated from a series of observations of both the independent and dependent variables.
    Author:
    Jonathon Hare (jsh2@ecs.soton.ac.uk)

    • Method Detail

      • estimate

        boolean estimate(List<? extends IndependentPair<I,D>> data)
        Estimates the model from the observations in the list of data. The data must contain at least numItemsToEstimate() pairs of dependent and independent data. It may contain more, in which case the estimate method may choose to make use of this data for validation, or obtaining a better model by a least squares method for example.
        Parameters:
        data - Data with which to estimate the model
        Returns:
        true if a successful estimate was made, false otherwise
        See Also:
        numItemsToEstimate()

      • numItemsToEstimate

        int numItemsToEstimate()
        Returns:
        The minimum number of observations required to estimate the model.
